Â§3. TRAUMA (PTSD/C-PTSD) GLOBAL PERSPECTIVES

3.1 Trauma in Cultural Context

Cultural variations in trauma:

Â· Individualistic cultures: Focus on personal trauma
Â· Collectivist cultures: Collective trauma, intergenerational trauma
Â· Conflict zones: Continuous trauma, survival mode as norm
Â· Diaspora communities: Displacement trauma plus acculturation stress

3.2 Culturally Informed Trauma Practices

Â· Safety definitions that respect cultural boundaries
Â· Healing practices that integrate cultural traditions
Â· Community support appropriate to cultural community structures
Â· Storytelling in culturally appropriate ways

3.3 Global Trauma Responses

Recognize that trauma responses are expressed differently across cultures:

Â· Somatization in some cultures
Â· Spiritual experiences in others
Â· Collective rather than individual symptoms

