Â§4. CHRONIC ILLNESS & DISABILITY WORLDWIDE

4.1 Disability Justice Across Cultures

Cultural models of disability:

Â· Medical model (Western): Individual deficit
Â· Social model: Societal barriers
Â· Cultural model: Varies by cultural interpretation
Â· Spiritual model: Karma, fate, spiritual lesson

Flow integrates all models while centering the node's experience.

4.2 Spoon Theory in Different Economic Contexts

Â· High-income countries: More resources but higher expectations
Â· Low-income countries: Fewer resources but different expectations
Â· Flow adaptation: Flexible participation, async options, energy-based planning

4.3 Accessibility as Cultural Practice

Â· Physical accessibility varies by infrastructure
Â· Digital accessibility varies by technology access
Â· Social accessibility varies by cultural norms

